    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 large eggs</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons milk</li>
            <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon butter or oil</li>
            <li>Optional toppings: grated cheese, chopped herbs, diced vegetables</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2> Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>eggs</li>
            <li>healthy</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, salt, and pepper until well combined.</li>
            <li>Heat butter or oil in a non-stick skillet over medium heat.</li>
            <li>Pour the egg mixture into the skillet and let it sit for a few seconds without stirring.</li>
            <li>Using a spatula, gently stir the eggs, pushing them from the edges toward the center.</li>
            <li>Continue stirring occasionally until the eggs are mostly set but still slightly runny.</li>
            <li>Remove the skillet from heat, as the residual heat will continue to cook the eggs to perfection.</li>
            <li>Optional: Sprinkle grated cheese, chopped herbs, or diced vegetables on top for added flavor.</li>
            <li>Serve the scrambled eggs hot and enjoy a quick and delicious breakfast!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

